24. What is composition?
Composition is a design concept where one class contains another class as a property.
means defining any other clas object inside a class.
<?php
class Engine {
    public function start() {
        echo "Engine started\n";
    }
}

class Car {
    private $engine;

    public function __construct() {
        $this->engine = new Engine(); // composition
    }

    public function startCar() {
        $this->engine->start();
        echo "Car started\n";
    }
}

// Usage
$car = new Car();
$car->startCar();
?>

25. Aggregation vs composition?
Composition → strong dependency, One class creates and owns another class  , If parent is destroyed → child is also destroyed
Aggregation → weak relationship, One class uses another class, but does NOT create it
<?php
class Engine {
    public function start() {
        echo "Engine started\n";
    }
}

class Car {
    private $engine;

    // Engine passed from outside → aggregation
    public function __construct(Engine $engine) {
        $this->engine = $engine;
    }

    public function startCar() {
        $this->engine->start();
        echo "Car started\n";
    }
}

// Engine exists independently
$engine = new Engine();
$car = new Car($engine);
$car->startCar();
?>

26. What is dependency injection?
Providing dependencies externally instead of creating inside class.
<?php
class Logger {
    public function log($msg) {
        echo "Log: $msg\n";
    }
}

class UserService {
    private $logger;

    // Dependency injected
    public function __construct(Logger $logger) {
        $this->logger = $logger;
    }

    public function createUser() {
        $this->logger->log("User created");
    }
}

// Inject dependency
$logger = new Logger();
$userService = new UserService($logger);
$userService->createUser();
?>


